Macros
Prerequisites for Macros

Before you create and run macros, ensure that your org meets the prerequisites. REQUIRED EDITIONS: 
Available in Salesforce Classic: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions 
Available in Lightning Experience: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions 

In Salesforce Classic, macros are supported on objects with both feed-based layouts and quick actions, including accounts, cases, contacts, and leads. You can only add the Macros widget to the Salesforce Console for Service.

In Lightning Experience, macros are supported on all standard objects except Campaign, and on custom objects that allow quick actions and have a customizable page layout. You can add the Macros utility to any Lightning app.

The following prerequisites apply:

* The record page must include a publisher and actions like Email or Log a Call.
* Add the Macros widget or utility to the app.
* Users must have the appropriate user permissions to create and run macros.
title: Prerequisites for Creating and Running Macros in Service Cloud
